.TH suspend  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBsuspend\fR \-  Suspends your script and returns to the Innovus prompt
.SH Syntax \fBsuspend\fR [-help] 
.P Suspends your script and returns to the Innovus prompt.
.P The suspend command gives you more flexibility in managing and debugging your scripts. You can insert multiple suspend commands in a script. The suspend command can also be used in nested scripts. When the script reaches a point where you have inserted the suspend command, it stops and restores access to the Innovus prompt. You can then type any command required for debugging.
.P Whenever you want to resume your script, just type resume at the Innovus prompt. 
.SH Parameters    "\fB-help\fR" Prints the usage of the suspend command.  For a detailed description of the command, use the man command: man suspend. 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 resume  "*" 2 "Interrupting the Software" section of the Getting Started chapter in the Innovus User Guide
.RE
.P
